enhance multi-agent collaborative inference by optimizing problem (P2). This is summarized in the following theorem.

Theorem 1. A policy update that minimizes the objective function of problem (P2) can also minimize the objective function of problem (P1) for small Œ≤.

Proof. We assume that the numbers of UEs and the task
number of each UE in the two problems are equal. For
convenience, we signify the objective function of problem (P1) and (p2) as f1(œÄ) and f2(œÄ), respectively. We denote the Ô¨Årst and the second terms in f1(œÄ) as A(œÄ) and B(œÄ), i.e., f1(œÄ) = A(œÄ) + Œ≤B(œÄ), and f2(œÄ) can be rewritten as:

