Fig. 3. Overall structure of MAHPPO. This algorithm contains multiple actor networks and a global critic network. At the left part, all vectors in the state are concatenated and sent to the actors and the critic. Each actor outputs the partitioning point, ofÔ¨Çoading channel, and transmit power decisions for its corresponding UE, and the critic outputs an estimation of the state value. The middle part depicts the loss function, where ‚Äúsurr‚Äù is short for ‚Äúsurrogate objective.‚Äù The right part illustrates how a trajectory for policy updating is obtained.

