where œÄŒ∏(at|st) is the current policy and œÄŒ∏old (at|st) is the old policy for collecting a trajectory. Furthermore, AÀÜt is the advantage function which measures how much a speciÔ¨Åc action at is better than the average actions at state st. This objective is called the ‚Äúsurrogate objective‚Äù because it uses the importance sampling trick to treat samples from the old policy as the surrogate of new samples to train the actors. In order to reduce bias of the advantage function, we employ an exponentially-weighting method to obtain the generalized advantage estimation [19]:

T (œÄ)
